    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Sand devised to blot wet ink after writing, used until approximately the mid 1800s as an alternative to blotting paper. Applied from a small shaker pot or box to speed the drying process, the excess sand would then be shaken off.</Note_Text>
